Using Tesseract for OCR

Install Tesseract:

For Ubuntu/Debian-based systems:
bash
Copy code
sudo apt-get install tesseract-ocr
For Windows, download the installer from the official GitHub page.
Open Terminal or Command Prompt:

On Linux, press Ctrl + Alt + T to open a terminal.
On Windows, press Win + R, type cmd, and press Enter.
Navigate to the image directory:

bash
Copy code
cd path/to/your/image/directory
Run Tesseract:

bash
Copy code
tesseract input_image.png output_text.txt
Replace input_image.png with your image file and output_text.txt with the desired output file name.

View the Output:
Open the generated text file to review the extracted text.

bash
Copy code
cat output_text.txt  # On Linux
type output_text.txt # On Windows

